The paper focuses on identifying fake news on social networks, specifically Twitter, which suggests that it falls under the categories of social networks (cs.SOC) and information retrieval (cs.IR). The use of reputation algorithms and crowdsourcing also suggests the categories of computational linguistics (cs.CL) and cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the paper deals with a large-scale study, which could also fall under the category of social computing (cs.SI).
